text: Anyasevo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Miyakibashevsky Selsoviet, Miyakinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 921 as of 2010. There are 11 streets. == Geography == It is located 13 km from Kirgiz-Miyaki. == References == Category:Rural localities in Miyakinsky District
title: Anyasevo
